F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdecided-raise-kids-family-near-grandparents-pros-and-cons-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraising%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20running%20a%20household%2C%20we%20lose%20touch%20with%20our%20professional%20identity.%20The%20loss%20of%20ourselves%20becomes%20a%20real%20obstacle%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20writing%20for%20a%20local%20parenting%20publication%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20month%20to%20flex%20my%20brain.%20Returning%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinance-jobs-highest-salaries-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinance%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20wasn't%20for%20me%2C%20and%20since%20I%20have%20a%20Journalism%20degree%20(and%20am%20a%20parent)%2C%20it%20made%20sense.%20But%20when%20my%20marriage%20got%20rocky%2C%20I%20felt%20trapped%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20financially%20dependent%20on%20my%20spouse.%20I%20wasn't%20confident%20in%20my%20ability%20to%20support%20myself%2C%20so%20I%20stayed%20put.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20had%20lost%20touch%20with%20myself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%202020%20hit%2C%20I%20fell%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fwhat-is-depression%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeep%20depression%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20only%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20In%20my%20marriage%2C%20I%20felt%20more%20like%20an%20employee%20than%20a%20partner%20or%20even%20a%20friend.%20I%20couldn't%20deal%20with%20the%20constant%20chaos%20of%20fighting%2C%20so%20I%20checked%20out%20emotionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fwhy-am-i-sleeping-so-much-all-of-a-sudden%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleeping%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20walking%20for%20hours%20every%20day%20to%20escape%2C%20and%20felt%20myself%20getting%20physically%20sick.%20I%20felt%20so%20drained%20and%20exhausted%20that%20I%20was%20sure%20I%20had%20an%20autoimmune%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20lost%20touch%20with%20so%20much%20of%20myself%20that%20I%20was%20afraid%20there'd%20be%20nothing%20of%20%26quot%3Bme%26quot%3B%20left%20soon.%20I%20needed%20out%20of%20my%20marriage.%20But%20that%20meant%20finding%20a%20way%20to%20support%20myself%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20convincing%20myself%20that%20I%20could.%20Driven%20by%20self-preservation%2C%20I%20hit%20the%20ground%20sprinting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20writing%20more%20and%20more%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBerger%20said%20experiencing%20evidence%20of%20your%20competence%20and%20capabilities%20helps%20build%20your%20relevance%20and%20confidence.%20She%20advises%20getting%20support%20from%20a%20professional%20or%20peer%20group%20to%20sharpen%20your%20focus%20on%20the%20kind%20of%20work%20you%20truly%20yearn%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20that's%20writing.%20I%20joined%20a%20few%20Facebook%20writing%20groups%20and%20signed%20up%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20online%20writing%20classes.%20I%20took%20a%20low-paying%20gig%20from%20a%20content%20mill%20writing%20non-bilined%20medical%20articles%20for%20popular%20health%20websites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20year%2C%20I%20pitched%20dozens%20of%20publications.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20I%20received%20a%20kind%20rejection%20or%20no%20response.%20But%20each%20time%20a%20new%20editor%20gave%20me%20a%20chance%2C%20it%20sparked%20the%20fire%20that%20kept%20me%20going.%20Landing%20my%20first%20major%20national%20byline%20in%202021%20%E2%80%94%20followed%20quickly%20succession%20by%20several%20more%20%E2%80%94%20gave%20me%20the%20self-assurance%20to%20break%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%2C%20I'm%20not%20'just'%20a%20mom%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20years%20later%2C%20I'm%20divorced%20and%20hustling.%20I%20take%20on%20as%20much%20work%20as%20possible%20because%20part%20of%20me%20is%20still%20terrified%20that%20I%20won't%20make%20it.%20I%20contribute%20regularly%20to%20a%20few%20publications%20and%20do%20part-time%20editorial%20work%20for%20a%20healthcare%20company.%20Making%20money%20has%20to%20take%20precedence%20over%20passion%20projects%2C%20which%20I%20need%20more%20time%20to%20pursue.%20That%20can%20be%20frustrating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerger%20emphasizes%20the%20importance%20of%20patience%20when%20you're%20juggling%20work%20with%20parenting%20%E2%80%94%20there%20may%20be%20weeks%2C%20months%2C%20or%20even%20years%20when%20you%20need%20to%20put%20some%20aspects%20of%20your%20career%20goals%20on%20a%20shelf.%20%26quot%3BLook%20at%20what%20you%20can%20accomplish%20across%2020%20or%2030%20years%20versus%20this%20year.%20If%20you%20allow%20yourself%20to%20keep%20moving%20and%20growing%2C%20you'll%20be%20totally%20ready%20and%20positioned%20for%20the%20next%20stage%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I'm%20not%20pursuing%20new%20bylines%20every%20week%2C%20working%20remotely%20and%20setting%20my%20schedule%20lets%20me%20show%20up%20for%20my%2010-year-old%20when%20he%20needs%20me.%20%26quot%3BMom%26quot%3B%20is%20no%20longer%20my%20sole%20role%20but%20is%20still%20the%20most%20important.%20I%20know%20this%20precious%20time%20during%20his%20childhood%20is%20limited.%20I%20feel%20guilty%20that%20I%20have%20to%20work%2C%20and%20on%20really%20tough%20days%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20a%20total%20failure.%20But%20my%20home%20is%20a%20safe%20space%20full%20of%20love%2C%20and%20that's%20not%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-change-forties-rewarding-hard-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714648861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663137ac0dfb1341e900d553%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-change-forties-rewarding-hard-2024-5%22