at%20work%20or%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20should%20be%20able%20to%20embrace%20unstructured%20time.%20Indeed%2C%20culturally%2C%20that's%20a%20norm%20that's%20declining%2C%20especially%20for%20kids.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2F23759898%2Fkids-children-parenting-play-anxiety-mental-health%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAs%20Vox's%20Anna%20North%20laid%20out%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20children's%20unstructured%20playtime%20in%20the%20US%20dropped%20by%2025%25%20from%201981%20to%201997.%20For%20various%20reasons%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-being-kid-is-different-now-than-it-was-20-years-ago%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekids%20don't%20have%20as%20much%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20getting%20along%20doing%20stuff%20on%20their%20own%20anymore%2C%20which%20can%20influence%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-parents-should-do-what-kids-want-on-vacation-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esense%20of%20autonomy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20deprive%20them%20of%20opportunities%20to%20develop%20important%20social%20skills%20and%20tools%20to%20combat%20anxiety%20and%20depression.%20It%20may%20also%20mean%20that%20as%20adults%2C%20they%20struggle%20to%20go%20with%20the%20flow.%20Perhaps%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20young%20adults%20who%20had%20their%20childhood%20activities%20scheduled%20down%20to%20the%20minute%20are%20embracing%20the%20PowerPoint%20party.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhobbies-death-side-hustles-remote-work-job-market-economic-precarity-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunstructured%20time%20is%20good%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20people%20of%20all%20ages.%20It%20can%20help%20with%20stress%20and%20anxiety%2C%20add%20space%20for%20rest%2C%20relaxation%2C%20and%20creativity%2C%20and%20give%20people%20a%20mental%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20embracing%20a%20bit%20more%20randomn