0of%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20M%20Nagaprasanna%20addressed%20the%20complexity%20of%20determining%20abetment%20of%20suicide%20in%20cases%20involving%20contentious%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20ruling%20stemmed%20from%20a%20petition%20involving%20allegations%20of%20abetment%20of%20suicide%20against%20a%20man%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20death%20of%20a%20priest%20in%20a%20church%20in%20Udupi%20in%20coastal%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%20was%20accused%20of%20triggering%20the%20priest's%20suicide%20by%20allegedly%20urging%20him%20to%20%26quot%3Bgo%20hang%20himself%26quot%3B%20during%20a%20conversation%20about%20the%20priest's%20alleged%20relationship%20with%20the%20petitioner's%20wife.%20The%20defence%20counsel%20argued%20that%20the%20statement%20was%20made%20out%20of%20anguish%20upon%20discovering%20the%20alleged%20affair%2C%20and%20the%20priest's%20decision%20to%20end%20his%20life%20was%20influenced%20by%20the%20affair%20becoming%20known%20to%20others%2C%20rather%20than%20solely%20by%20the%20accused's%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposing%20counsel%20contended%20that%20the%20priest%20took%20his%20own%20life%20due%20to%20the%20accused's%20threatening%20language%20about%20exposing%20the%20affair.%20However%2C%20the%20single%20judge%20bench%2C%20drawing%20on%20precedents%20set%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20emphasised%20that%20such%20statements%20alone%20might%20not%20constitute%20abetment%20to%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20acknowledged%20the%20multifaceted%20reasons%20behind%20the%20priest's%20suicide%2C%20including%20the%20alleged%20illicit%20relationship%20he%20had%20despite%20his%20role%20as%20a%20father%20and%20priest.%20Recognising%20the%20complexities%20of%20human%20psychology%2C%20the%20court%20underscored%20the%20challenge%20of%20deciphering%20the%20human%20mind%20and%20declined%20to%20categorise%20the%20accused's%20statement%20as%20abetment%20to%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECons